
[1]aback

   ABACK, adv. [At, on or towards the back. See Back]

   Towards the back; on the back part; backward. In seamen's language it
   signifies the situation of the sails, when pressed back against the
   mast by the wind.

   Taken aback, is when the sails are carried back suddenly by the wind.

   Laid aback, is when the sails are purposely placed in that situation to
   give the ship sternway.
